# Engineering Guides (`documents/`)

This repo holds **backend API, data, throughput, and deploy** reference guides. Each guide has a `README.md` (table of contents) and `includes/*.md` (full articles).

## Before finishing any doc change

1. Update guide README TOC when adding, renaming, or removing `includes/*.md`
2. Use correct cross-link paths (`../` from README, `../../` from includes)
3. Run validation from repo root:

```bash
make validate    # links, anchors, README TOC, prose lint
make check       # validate + acronym check
```

After bulk TOC or GLOSSARY edits: `make github-format`

## File layout

```
guide-name/
├── README.md
└── includes/
    └── NN-topic.md
```

Root index: [README.md](../README.md). Conventions: [CONTRIBUTING.md](../CONTRIBUTING.md).

## Agent behavior

- Prefer **editing existing includes** over new top-level guides
- Link to sibling guides instead of duplicating full algorithms
- No `TODO` / placeholder sections — ship complete content or don't add the file
- Do not create commits unless the user asks
